BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2vBb5fWGswsn0pg99N2rM
SUMMARY:Scout Day at the Garden for Younger Scouts
DTSTAMP:20260406T030455Z
DTSTART:20260419T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Come and work on scout badges and achievement requirements at t
	he Botanical Garden! Designed for K-3rd grade Girl Scouts and Cub Scouts\,
	 Scouts will visit stations in the Education Center and go on a nature wal
	k. Some of the topics include: composting with worms\, insects\, Leave No 
	Trace\, planting seeds\, and pollination. Scouts will receive a garden fun
	 patch and a list of completed activities towards their badges or achievem
	ents. \n\nTo make the check-in process smoother\, we are asking 2nd and 3r
	d graders to come at 12:20 pm at the earliest\, and K-1st graders to come 
	at 12:45 pm.  If you have a mix of ages\, anytime between 12:30 and 12:45 
	is fine.  You can leave when you are done. Adult chaperones are free.  Ema
	il Us with any questions or to register a group. \n\n$12 per scout.\n\nhtt
	ps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scout-day-at-the-garden-for-you
	nger-scouts/18185400/2026-04-19T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scout-day-at-the-garden-f
	or-younger-scouts/18185400/2026-04-19T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
